01:06.700 --> 01:08.277
<i>I think we can begin.</i>

01:08.827 --> 01:11.274
<i>The first parole request</i>
<i>for Carter "Doc" McCoy.</i>

01:11.378 --> 01:12.819
<i>Is legal counsel present?</i>

01:12.923 --> 01:16.034
Yes, sir. I'm Eugene Stewart,
representing Mr. McCoy.

01:21.965 --> 01:25.464
<i>" Carter McCoy, one to ten year sentence</i>
<i>for armed robbery.</i>

01:26.094 --> 01:28.585
<i>" First offense in the state of Texas.</i>

01:29.305 --> 01:31.836
"Wanted by the state of Ohio
for assault with a deadly weapon...

01:31.940 --> 01:33.087
<i>"...and armed robbery."</i>

01:33.192 --> 01:36.387
The State of Ohio has waived jurisdiction,
Mr. Chairman.

01:36.771 --> 01:39.523
<i>Mr. McCoy is no longer wanted</i>
<i>in that case.</i>

01:43.445 --> 01:44.725
Good luck, man.

01:45.697 --> 01:47.100
<i>Mr. McCoy has served</i>
<i>four years of his sentence.</i>

01:47.205 --> 01:48.942
<i>His record's satisfactory.</i>

01:49.534 --> 01:52.535
<i>Applied for parole</i>
<i>on September fifth of this year.</i>

01:54.831 --> 01:55.858
<i>Remarks?</i>

01:55.962 --> 01:58.485
I would only, once again,
like to point out to the committee...

01:58.589 --> 02:01.154
...Mr. McCoy's good behavior
while a prisoner.

02:01.258 --> 02:03.368
- Notice is taken.
- Thank you, sir.

02:03.472 --> 02:06.037
The board met
in closed chambers last week.

02:06.258 --> 02:10.164
Have you reached a decision regarding
Mr. McCoy's request for parole?

02:10.269 --> 02:12.219
Request for parole is denied.

02:12.431 --> 02:15.800
The prisoner may re-apply
after one calendar year.

03:36.723 --> 03:38.052
Lock 'em up.

04:31.778 --> 04:33.236
<i>Open the gate.</i>

04:46.793 --> 04:50.458
Lance said to have eight hole,
Gallo one, Kirksky two.

04:51.214 --> 04:52.672
Eight hole colored.

04:53.173 --> 04:56.791
Go down to the garden house,
turn to your left, go to the woods.

04:56.968 --> 05:01.215
<i>We're going on to the brush. Burn it.</i>
<i>Take the stumps up out of the ground.</i>

05:01.431 --> 05:04.634
Bob Field, get them dogs out there
close to the trailer.

05:24.121 --> 05:25.200
One hole.

05:34.339 --> 05:35.502
Eight hole.

05:43.974 --> 05:45.016
Thirty.

05:45.517 --> 05:46.560
Thirty.

05:48.019 --> 05:49.062
Come on.

05:49.728 --> 05:51.851
- Fifteen.
- Fifteen.

05:55.193 --> 05:57.767
Get them dogs in close to 'em, Bob Field.

06:22.554 --> 06:24.048
- Thirty.
- Thirty.

06:28.685 --> 06:32.131
Hogfield, you go to the left
and start rounding up on that brush pile.

06:32.236 --> 06:33.428
Time to go.

06:34.983 --> 06:37.308
<i>Put it back. Catch them, this squad.</i>

06:38.612 --> 06:41.150
<i>Round this pile up and get it burning.</i>

06:44.785 --> 06:46.741
Oh, man, that's just a game.

06:50.081 --> 06:51.990
Man, get on this stump.

06:53.417 --> 06:55.042
Look out, McCoy.

06:55.586 --> 06:58.338
Get your axe and come on up here
and pitch in.

07:00.966 --> 07:03.042
Go to work. Go to work.

07:09.225 --> 07:11.763
<i>De Leon, get the fire going.</i>

07:13.020 --> 07:14.764
That Mexican there...

07:14.897 --> 07:17.981
Get up all this little stuff
and put it on this pile.

07:21.153 --> 07:22.196
Thirty.

07:22.446 --> 07:23.609
Eight hole.

07:23.781 --> 07:26.616
Catch that brush pile here
and get it rounded up.

07:26.742 --> 07:30.989
I want it tight to where it'll burn.
Get these stumps down under the ground.

07:33.874 --> 07:35.072
Bob Field...

07:35.459 --> 07:37.084
<i>...round up that pile.</i>

07:37.211 --> 07:40.082
<i>Get it to burn.</i>
<i>Kirk Shaw, over on the ground...</i>

07:47.220 --> 07:48.880
Keep that line straight.

07:52.517 --> 07:54.059
<i>Keep that line tight.</i>

08:48.531 --> 08:49.776
Hello, Doc.

08:59.709 --> 09:00.824
I'm sorry.

09:05.131 --> 09:06.408
Get to Beynon.

09:06.512 --> 09:08.915
Tell him I'm for sale. His price.

09:12.514 --> 09:13.712
Do it now.

09:26.778 --> 09:28.402
Hello, Mrs. McCoy.

09:29.197 --> 09:31.071
I'd like to see Jack Beynon.

09:35.787 --> 09:36.901
Go ahead.

09:41.917 --> 09:43.321
Class. Is she a regular?

09:43.425 --> 09:45.577
No. Doc McCoy's old lady.

09:45.963 --> 09:47.616
Jeez, is that Carol Ainsley?

09:47.721 --> 09:49.043
Shut up!

09:52.511 --> 09:54.254
How are you, Mrs. McCoy?

09:56.098 --> 09:58.671
Ready to talk about my husband,
Mr. Beynon.

10:01.311 --> 10:02.770
Please sit down.

10:07.484 --> 10:09.691
So the good doctor comes up again.

10:12.823 --> 10:14.899
He asked me to come and see you.

10:16.493 --> 10:17.493
Why?

10:19.538 --> 10:20.701
Can I help?

10:23.417 --> 10:25.041
Yes, I think you can.

10:30.215 --> 10:31.626
How about a drink?

10:32.800 --> 10:34.425
Yeah, I could use one.

10:35.470 --> 10:36.715
Come on over.

10:59.536 --> 11:01.078
You'll be back, Doc.

11:39.909 --> 11:42.661
Mr. Beynon will see you
the day after tomorrow.

11:42.995 --> 11:45.118
12:30 at the River Walk.

12:37.466 --> 12:38.960
- Hi, Doc.
- Hi.

12:41.261 --> 12:42.340
Feel okay?

12:42.929 --> 12:45.717
I'm a lot better off now
than I was an hour ago.

12:48.393 --> 12:51.430
- You want to drive?
- My driver's license has expired.

12:55.650 --> 12:58.559
Sorry I'm late. I was having my hair done,
the girl was slow.

12:58.663 --> 12:59.934
You look fine.

13:02.199 --> 13:03.823
- You feel good?
- Yeah.

13:06.370 --> 13:08.826
- Where do you want to go?
- Take a walk.

15:45.528 --> 15:47.437
What do you want for dinner?

15:48.531 --> 15:50.856
Drinks. Whiskey, whiskey, whiskey...

16:36.202 --> 16:37.317
You okay?

16:38.663 --> 16:39.944
Pretty good.

16:40.915 --> 16:43.318
Made a trip to Oregon
to see my brother and his kids.

16:43.422 --> 16:45.321
I figured it'd be
the last time I'd see them...

16:45.425 --> 16:47.543
...unless they decide to travel.

16:47.839 --> 16:49.167
How's Estelle?

16:49.591 --> 16:50.670
Fatter.

16:52.719 --> 16:54.877
You know, some things never change.

16:56.598 --> 16:58.092
Yeah, that's right.

17:00.518 --> 17:02.096
That's not all of it.

17:04.314 --> 17:06.105
It's been a long time, Doc.

17:07.525 --> 17:09.066
Did you go out much?

17:10.819 --> 17:13.357
Four years, and now
the question comes up.

17:23.874 --> 17:25.782
I couldn't handle it inside.

17:26.210 --> 17:27.454
But I can now.

17:28.754 --> 17:30.296
I'm still here, Doc.

19:09.645 --> 19:11.887
It does something to you, you know.

19:13.274 --> 19:14.982
It does something to you.

19:18.154 --> 19:20.312
It does something to you in there.

19:30.666 --> 19:33.069
We've got time, Doc.
We've got lots of time.

19:33.173 --> 19:35.078
Just give me a minute, baby.

19:36.172 --> 19:38.580
Listen, I'm just as nervous as you are.

19:40.885 --> 19:42.048
Really?

19:42.261 --> 19:43.506
Really.

19:47.058 --> 19:49.216
Let me make you feel good, Doctor.

20:00.862 --> 20:02.689
It's been so long.

20:04.908 --> 20:06.236
So long.

20:28.182 --> 20:29.380
Fantastic.

20:34.981 --> 20:36.226
She's here.

20:40.570 --> 20:42.352
Hey, I was gonna fix you breakfast.

20:42.456 --> 20:43.811
You were sleeping.

20:43.916 --> 20:45.317
A little ketchup.

20:50.329 --> 20:52.239
And then we have a little...

21:00.756 --> 21:01.835
Thank you.

21:04.176 --> 21:06.168
- For what?
- For getting me out.

21:08.680 --> 21:10.139
It was a pleasure.

21:20.567 --> 21:21.942
Thank you, ma'am.

21:26.448 --> 21:29.021
Hey, Claude. Here's your boy.

21:39.628 --> 21:41.115
You have to be kidding.

21:41.219 --> 21:44.463
Not at all.
Just a pleasant way to have lunch.

21:45.050 --> 21:46.164
Sit down.

21:49.012 --> 21:51.414
It's good to see you
in them civilian clothes.

21:51.518 --> 21:53.637
It just takes a long arm, Beynon.

21:55.643 --> 21:58.644
You know, it's hard to say
how those things happen.

21:59.939 --> 22:02.975
The parole board almost never
changes their decision.

22:04.026 --> 22:06.517
It must be because I'm a model prisoner.

22:08.739 --> 22:11.491
This is the only time
you and I meet in public.

22:12.660 --> 22:14.320
Any business with me...

22:14.912 --> 22:16.649
...you handle it with him.

22:16.753 --> 22:18.289
He's my brother.

22:19.667 --> 22:21.659
Back with your own people, now.

22:21.836 --> 22:23.793
I got you some professionals.

22:24.338 --> 22:26.247
I'll get my own men, Beynon.

22:29.009 --> 22:31.679
You run the job, but I run the show.

22:32.138 --> 22:33.632
And don't forget it.

22:39.353 --> 22:41.513
You've got two weeks to set it up.

22:42.566 --> 22:46.694
It's not a big bank, but it handles
the cash deposits for an oil company.

22:47.696 --> 22:49.604
Over half a million dollars.

22:50.781 --> 22:52.275
It's a family bank.

22:52.908 --> 22:54.273
The brother of the bank director...

22:54.378 --> 22:57.867
...is on the board of directors
at Con-Sol Oil in Beacon City.

23:05.588 --> 23:08.375
Here's a couple of fellas
I'd like you to meet.

23:09.550 --> 23:11.377
Rudy Butler, Frank Jackson.

23:17.725 --> 23:19.423
Yeah, I've heard of you.

23:19.528 --> 23:21.096
You work with Miller?

23:21.771 --> 23:23.479
You're out of touch, Doc.

23:23.939 --> 23:25.517
Miller got blown up.

23:28.903 --> 23:29.945
Where?

23:30.738 --> 23:32.113
Fort Lauderdale.

23:33.157 --> 23:34.865
- Were you with him?
- Yeah.

23:36.952 --> 23:38.067
I got out.

23:39.663 --> 23:40.663
You?

23:41.540 --> 23:43.699
I was backup man on a payroll job.

23:45.293 --> 23:47.030
I'd hit some liquor stores. I drive good.

23:47.134 --> 23:48.243
I drive.

23:49.839 --> 23:50.839
Sure.

23:52.926 --> 23:55.298
I want Mexican visas and passports.

23:55.845 --> 23:57.423
They'll be ready.

23:58.264 --> 24:00.008
You boys just do your job.

24:08.108 --> 24:09.187
Carol.

24:10.568 --> 24:12.027
Bank guard, 7:59.

24:12.404 --> 24:13.602
He's early.

24:21.996 --> 24:24.570
You got a flashlight, some light batteries.

24:25.291 --> 24:27.961
A-hooks, pliers, wire cutters...

24:33.049 --> 24:35.291
What do you want all this stuff for?

24:35.635 --> 24:38.173
- I'm going on a picnic.
- Going on a picnic?

24:39.013 --> 24:40.424
Well... okay.

24:47.146 --> 24:50.978
<i>And now, ladies and gentlemen,</i>
<i>especially you gentlemen...</i>

24:51.316 --> 24:55.610
<i>We very proudly present</i>
<i>the pride and Joy of Beacon City.</i>

24:55.904 --> 24:58.934
<i>Our own high-stepping and high-kicking...</i>

24:59.039 --> 25:01.191
<i>...Southwest Texas Ropers.</i>

25:24.476 --> 25:28.254
<i>Following the strutters...</i>
<i>representing the Ladies' Auxiliary</i> of...

25:28.359 --> 25:32.648
<i>...the Volunteer Fire Brigade.</i>
<i>We have the first beautiful float...</i>

25:32.942 --> 25:37.272
<i>...which consists of the Constitution</i>
<i>in the history of the Lone Star State.</i>

25:53.670 --> 25:54.780
Good morning.

25:54.884 --> 25:57.078
I'd like an application
for a checking account, please.

25:57.182 --> 26:00.998
He goes here, follows down here.
Now, this is the spot you're looking for.

26:01.102 --> 26:02.340
Here. Yeah.

26:02.471 --> 26:04.677
- Can I get a copy of this?
- Yes, sir.

26:14.274 --> 26:16.232
- Thanks a lot.
- You're welcome.

26:38.297 --> 26:40.089
Change for a $50, please.

26:45.471 --> 26:47.380
$20, $30...

26:48.141 --> 26:50.845
...$40, $45, $50.

26:52.103 --> 26:54.724
Thank you.
Y'all come back and see us soon.

26:57.150 --> 26:59.819
Set your clocks for five minutes after 9:00.

27:01.487 --> 27:03.480
All right, on the nose, now.

27:04.907 --> 27:07.521
The diversionary explosions are spaced
20 seconds apart.

27:07.626 --> 27:09.029
That gives you...

27:09.662 --> 27:12.414
...one minute and 38 seconds,
before they blow.

27:15.626 --> 27:18.663
You've got a bank president,
you have three tellers.

27:20.131 --> 27:21.663
And you've got a bank guard.

27:21.767 --> 27:23.079
Usually on the right as you come in.

27:23.183 --> 27:24.670
Pin him right away.

27:24.802 --> 27:27.590
Careful he doesn't panic,
and go shoot somebody.

27:29.057 --> 27:32.057
You got one local police car.
Now he's a rover.

27:32.602 --> 27:35.715
Shouldn't be anywhere near the vicinity
when we make our hit.

27:35.820 --> 27:37.883
Traffic is usually light at that hour.

27:37.987 --> 27:41.223
There are three exits. One at Hopkins,
one at Guadalupe Street...

27:41.327 --> 27:42.972
...and then there's the alley.

27:43.077 --> 27:45.608
Will you put that away and pay attention!

27:49.285 --> 27:51.194
Now the guard carries a.38.

27:53.289 --> 27:56.290
The cops carry 357-magnums.

27:59.962 --> 28:01.587
You know what this is.

28:02.965 --> 28:05.587
This'll stop an M-2 army rifle at 50 yards.

28:08.763 --> 28:11.254
I've been working ten years without one.

28:13.559 --> 28:15.635
- Suit yourself.
- Thank you.

28:16.354 --> 28:17.591
What about the vault?

28:17.696 --> 28:18.926
It's a Chambers Reilly.

28:19.030 --> 28:22.098
It's on a time lock.
Opens up 20 minutes before office hours.

28:22.202 --> 28:23.203
Wire pull over?

28:23.308 --> 28:26.065
No, one-inch stuff
on a three number combination.

28:26.197 --> 28:27.359
That's me.

28:27.697 --> 28:31.280
No, no. I'll handle the fine stuff.
You're backup all the way.

28:32.702 --> 28:34.529
Whatever you need, brother.

28:35.330 --> 28:36.445
Right.

28:39.376 --> 28:42.626
You keep going over this.
I don't want anybody lost.

28:43.338 --> 28:46.036
If we're clean,
Gollie will take us across at Laredo.

28:46.140 --> 28:49.252
If we're hot, we'll have to try Laughlin's
in El Paso.

28:53.724 --> 28:55.882
Aren't we going a little bit hard?

29:01.648 --> 29:03.439
That's a walk-in bank, man.

29:04.067 --> 29:05.396
A piece of cake.

29:07.571 --> 29:10.240
You don't have to be Dillinger for that one.

29:16.830 --> 29:17.830
Bang.

29:28.758 --> 29:30.335
Dillinger got killed.

29:33.554 --> 29:34.929
Not in the bank.

29:38.893 --> 29:40.351
Take it with you.

30:01.333 --> 30:02.447
Expenses.

30:08.632 --> 30:12.083
Tell Beynon I don't want any mix-ups.
I make one phone call.

30:13.220 --> 30:15.841
And his people better be there.
All of them.

30:18.266 --> 30:19.304
I understand.

30:19.408 --> 30:20.629
Beynon's to be alone at the drop.

30:20.733 --> 30:23.718
Only one car in the garage
at the ranch and that's it.

30:23.822 --> 30:25.299
Now, I'm not gonna have the money.

30:25.404 --> 30:29.312
And she's not gonna know where it is
until I know I'm clear. Got it?

30:30.194 --> 30:32.015
- He understands.
- Good, good.

30:32.119 --> 30:34.401
Make sure everybody does. Okay?

31:28.376 --> 31:30.369
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

31:33.006 --> 31:34.915
Good morning.

31:35.884 --> 31:37.082
Good morning.

31:45.602 --> 31:46.800
Good morning.

31:50.065 --> 31:52.467
Good morning, Mr. Morgan. How are you?

31:52.571 --> 31:53.895
Fine, thank you.

33:03.722 --> 33:04.764
Hold it.

33:27.327 --> 33:28.703
Come on, move it!

34:05.282 --> 34:06.361
Relax.

34:23.299 --> 34:25.706
Superior technology, my ass.

34:37.938 --> 34:39.315
Hands up!

34:46.657 --> 34:48.364
Mr. President? Up!

34:54.373 --> 34:56.199
Everybody, out this way.

35:01.338 --> 35:04.587
Come on, come on! Hurry it up! Move it!

35:07.468 --> 35:08.468
Go!

35:14.267 --> 35:16.094
Come on, move it!

35:20.481 --> 35:22.225
Come on, honey, get on it.

35:40.001 --> 35:42.040
Now just relax.

35:42.628 --> 35:43.957
Face down!

36:01.188 --> 36:03.311
Move it. Move it, honey.

36:05.692 --> 36:07.981
They're on their way. Just relax.

36:09.905 --> 36:11.315
Everybody relax.

37:02.999 --> 37:04.244
Ninety seconds.

37:30.235 --> 37:31.278
Seventy-five.

37:36.491 --> 37:37.654
Sixty-five.

37:41.037 --> 37:42.318
Fifty, brother.

37:54.675 --> 37:55.675
No!

37:55.926 --> 37:56.926
No!

38:05.436 --> 38:06.716
Stupid bastard!

38:26.499 --> 38:27.779
Take the wheel.

38:28.250 --> 38:29.531
Take the wheel.

38:58.738 --> 38:59.931
How did it go?

39:00.035 --> 39:02.273
Bad. Jackson killed the guard.

39:09.457 --> 39:12.079
Fourteen seconds till the next one goes off.

39:14.254 --> 39:16.246
Come on, come on.

40:11.311 --> 40:12.311
Shit.

41:48.614 --> 41:49.944
Where's Jackson?

41:51.452 --> 41:52.910
He didn't make it.

41:53.412 --> 41:54.823
Neither did you.

43:44.521 --> 43:47.180
<i>...was held up this morning</i>
<i>shortly after opening.</i>

43:47.284 --> 43:51.686
<i>The bank officials state that $750,000</i>
<i>was taken by three masked men...</i>

43:52.028 --> 43:53.066
<i>...who forced the employees...</i>

43:53.170 --> 43:55.186
Hey, there's only $500,000 here.

43:55.290 --> 43:57.239
- You sure?
- Yes, I'm sure.

44:00.495 --> 44:01.495
Doc?

44:02.122 --> 44:04.079
I see it. Take it easy.

44:04.291 --> 44:06.746
They're looking for three men, remember?

44:21.601 --> 44:23.973
What seems to be the problem, Officer?

44:28.940 --> 44:30.221
Okay, drive on.

45:02.766 --> 45:04.011
I'll kill him.

45:05.602 --> 45:07.180
I'll kill that mother!

45:15.028 --> 45:16.107
He's on.

45:17.739 --> 45:18.854
I'm here.

45:20.575 --> 45:21.575
Yeah?

45:23.120 --> 45:25.519
<i>Yeah?</i>

45:25.788 --> 45:26.867
I'm here.

45:42.221 --> 45:43.680
They checked in.

45:56.986 --> 45:58.768
Tell me about Beynon's ranch.

45:58.872 --> 46:00.523
I've never been there.

46:01.574 --> 46:03.697
When we met, it was at his office.

46:09.415 --> 46:10.874
Do you trust him?

46:11.917 --> 46:14.154
I don't figure he's gonna try to cross us.

46:14.258 --> 46:16.578
At least not until he gets his money.

46:16.839 --> 46:19.959
Well, let's just send his cut back
and just get going.

46:22.594 --> 46:25.085
If we make a mistake, he's gonna burn us.

46:25.472 --> 46:28.169
You make a deal,
you're better off keeping up your end.

46:28.273 --> 46:30.057
I don't want to go there.

46:32.103 --> 46:33.597
Let's do it my way.

47:12.478 --> 47:13.557
Stay here.

47:15.523 --> 47:17.681
I'll wrap it up as quick as I can.

48:01.526 --> 48:03.435
News said two people killed.

48:03.611 --> 48:06.019
Three. Rudy got ambitious.

48:06.489 --> 48:07.900
And you got him.

48:09.075 --> 48:10.268
That's right.

48:10.372 --> 48:12.028
What about your wife?

48:12.871 --> 48:14.108
Let's cut up the money, Beynon.

48:14.213 --> 48:15.782
I want to get north.

48:17.166 --> 48:19.407
She told me no one would get killed.

48:29.511 --> 48:31.171
I'm in a hurry, Beynon.

48:31.388 --> 48:33.879
You still don't get the picture, do you?

48:34.725 --> 48:37.892
And I've always heard
what a smart-ass operator you was.

48:38.228 --> 48:39.473
No applause.

