a lot of promises.

49:47.172 --> 49:48.215
Close.

49:48.757 --> 49:50.168
I wouldn't feel...

52:04.349 --> 52:05.392
Stupid!

52:06.518 --> 52:08.427
Why didn't you tell me, huh?

52:08.603 --> 52:10.219
Why didn't you tell me?

52:10.323 --> 52:12.602
There wasn't any way to explain it.

52:18.822 --> 52:20.779
You sent me to him, you know.

52:30.333 --> 52:32.456
What the hell do you want anyway?

52:53.982 --> 52:55.227
Goddamn you!

53:17.880 --> 53:19.208
Still no answer.

53:19.715 --> 53:21.126
Something's wrong.

53:22.885 --> 53:25.341
Come on! Come on!

53:30.851 --> 53:32.310
What's the damage?

53:34.688 --> 53:37.091
Your collarbone's broken
but it's not shattered.

53:37.195 --> 53:38.982
There's no infection, yet.

53:39.318 --> 53:42.023
Those bandages ought
to be changed twice a day.

53:43.030 --> 53:44.228
It's okay.

53:44.865 --> 53:46.657
I got a nurse in mind.

53:49.830 --> 53:52.451
The three of us are gonna
do some traveling.

53:54.917 --> 53:57.206
We're gonna take your car to El Paso.

53:58.337 --> 54:00.377
We... we can't leave here.

54:02.800 --> 54:05.671
That's not possible.
I mean, we have all of this.

54:09.640 --> 54:11.680
Is that possible, Mrs. Clinton?

54:13.936 --> 54:15.810
Just tell us what you want.

54:22.653 --> 54:24.435
What kind of a car do you drive?

54:24.539 --> 54:26.273
A Ford. We have a Ford.

54:31.495 --> 54:32.740
That's good.

54:35.082 --> 54:36.826
That's very good, Harold.

54:37.626 --> 54:39.868
You run on out and gas up the Ford.

54:41.172 --> 54:44.173
If anybody but you comes back, Harold...

54:45.676 --> 54:47.716
...she gets her clock stopped.

54:52.640 --> 54:54.680
You do what he says, Harold.

54:55.685 --> 54:57.096
Just do as I say.

55:14.996 --> 55:17.238
You. Get a cloth.

55:18.291 --> 55:19.869
You're gonna wash me.

55:26.424 --> 55:28.455
They still may be on the way to Laredo.

55:28.560 --> 55:31.386
What about El Paso?
He's a friend of Laughlin.

55:32.013 --> 55:33.289
Well, we have to cover them both.

55:33.394 --> 55:35.459
We've got to get somebody down there.
Either Rudy or...

55:35.564 --> 55:37.931
...McCoy's got a half a million bucks.

55:38.186 --> 55:40.392
- Put out the word.
- What about Jack?

55:42.232 --> 55:44.718
Just dump him down a dry well,
if you can find one.

55:44.822 --> 55:46.941
No, he ought to be buried proper.

55:48.320 --> 55:50.229
You just do what I tell you.

55:53.158 --> 55:54.569
Thank you, ma'am.

55:58.622 --> 56:00.164
Wendy, sit down.

56:02.042 --> 56:04.165
Two day-coach tickets to El Paso.

56:09.675 --> 56:13.009
Leaves in 45 minutes. Gate three.
Thank you, ma'am.

57:14.865 --> 57:16.573
Kind of tricky, isn't it?

57:22.748 --> 57:24.539
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

57:39.223 --> 57:40.551
Come over here.

57:57.240 --> 57:59.778
You don't always have to
take your gun out.

58:02.578 --> 58:04.405
I'll do anything you want.

58:05.748 --> 58:06.791
Really.

58:07.458 --> 58:08.501
I will.

58:14.048 --> 58:15.957
Get rid of that nail polish.

58:17.552 --> 58:18.552
Okay.

58:18.761 --> 58:20.172
I don't like it.

58:32.942 --> 58:34.650
And get rid of that, too.

58:35.487 --> 58:36.685
What is that?

59:00.428 --> 59:02.966
Don't get any blood on me. I hate blood.

59:12.398 --> 59:15.352
Say, you wouldn't happen to be
a Mormon, would you?

59:16.903 --> 59:18.390
No, I'm afraid not.

59:18.494 --> 59:19.597
I'd like another one.

59:19.701 --> 59:20.978
Me, neither.

59:21.532 --> 59:24.202
I'm from Orem. That's right near Salt Lake.

59:25.036 --> 59:29.365
There's about 12 people in the state who
aren't Mormons, and I'm one of them.

59:32.043 --> 59:34.449
I guess that makes you kind of special.

59:35.295 --> 59:37.868
- Yeah, I guess it does.
- Thank you.

59:38.715 --> 59:39.913
Hey, baby.

59:42.511 --> 59:45.041
You wouldn't be taking the train
to Salt Lake, would you?

59:45.146 --> 59:46.680
No, I'm afraid not!

59:47.015 --> 59:48.380
That's just my luck.

59:48.484 --> 59:50.296
Listen, I hope you have a really nice trip.

59:50.400 --> 59:52.635
Thanks. I hope yours is okay, too.

59:56.233 --> 59:57.470
Where's the bag?

59:57.575 --> 59:59.441
It's in the locker. I've got the key.

01:00:38.274 --> 01:00:39.301
A man helped me open it.

01:00:39.405 --> 01:00:40.687
How long ago?

01:00:41.444 --> 01:00:42.986
Fifteen minutes ago.

01:00:48.117 --> 01:00:51.782
It's the oldest con game in the world.
He switched keys with you.

01:00:56.792 --> 01:00:59.740
He'll figure you for more time.
He's probably still in the station.

01:00:59.844 --> 01:01:00.953
Find him.

